# Secret handling

- Secrets are referenced via environment variables, never hardcoded or logged.
- Commit `.env.example` with placeholders only.
- Do not print, echo, or include secret values in code, logs, tests, or docs.
- CI must run with zero secrets; live LLM calls belong in local-only scripts.
- If a secret might have leaked, stop and flag the operator before continuing.
